@startuml generator-stub-class
' Solution class diagram — Pass E: closure-bounding + link-stubbing + Frappe-core handling
' Architect, 2026-06-21. REV 2 — post critique pass 1 (E3 edge-kind split; E2-trust + E5 conditions).
' Design only. Reuses the Pass D generator (adr-generator.md) intact.
'
' Legend:
'   (NEW)   = net-new symbol introduced by this pass
'   (EDIT)  = existing symbol gains a small, named change
'   (REUSE) = existing symbol used unchanged
'
' THE E3 CORRECTION (critique blocker): Table/Table-MultiSelect targets are CHILD
' doctypes whose ROWS ARE the seed's data -> they must be generated FULL (transitively).
' ONLY Link targets are stubbed. Stubbing a child = framework-cols-only table =
' #saveChildren writes to missing columns = data loss.

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
hide empty members

' ===========================================================================
' GENERATOR LAYER  (src/generator/ + scripts/) — additive, pure transforms
' ===========================================================================
package "generator (src/generator)" {

  class "select-doctypes.js" as Sel {
    +listAllDoctypeFiles(root) : string[]   <<REUSE>>
    +closureOver(seeds, root, opts) : string[]   <<REUSE — kept behind --closure>>
    -_depsOf(json) : {link[],table[]}   <<REUSE — already splits edge kinds>>
    --
    .. NEW — bounded mode (E3, edge-kind split) ..
    +planInstall(seeds, root, opts) : InstallPlan   <<NEW>>
  }

  class "InstallPlan" as Plan <<NEW>> {
    +full  : string[]   ' seeds + ALL transitive Table/Table-MultiSelect targets -> generated FULLY
    +stubs : string[]   ' every LINK target of any FULL doctype, minus full -> stubbed
    .. invariants ..
    ' full and stubs are DISJOINT
    ' Table edges followed to CLOSURE (children + grandchildren full)
    ' Link edges CUT at the full-set boundary (depth bound = Links only)
    ' THROWS if a Table target has no JSON (dead-end guard — never stub a child)
  }

  class "erpnext-to-def.js" as E2D {
    +isRealDoctype(json) : boolean   <<REUSE>>
    +mapField(f) : FieldDef|null   <<REUSE>>
    +erpnextJsonToDef(json) : Def   <<REUSE — full defs (seeds + Table children)>>
    --
    .. NEW — synthesize a stub def for a LINK target (no source JSON) ..
    +makeStubDef(doctypeName) : Def   <<NEW>>
  }

  class "fieldtype-map.js" as FTM {
    +mapFieldtype(t) : Classified   <<REUSE>>
  }
}

' ===========================================================================
' CLI  (scripts/) — I/O layer, orchestrates the bounded install
' ===========================================================================
class "generate-doctypes.mjs" as CLI <<EDIT>> {
  ' modes: --stub-deps (NEW default) | --closure | --no-closure  (mutually exclusive)
  +main()   <<EDIT: --stub-deps -> planInstall; full via erpnextJsonToDef, stubs via makeStubDef>>
}

' ===========================================================================
' API VALIDATION  (src/validation/) — E2-trust condition (privilege key)
' ===========================================================================
class "request-schemas.js" as ReqS <<EDIT>> {
  +RESERVED_KEYS : Set   <<EDIT: add 'is_stub' (was owner/docstatus/name)>>
  +CreatePayloadSchema / UpdatePatchSchema   <<REUSE — run rejectReservedKeys>>
  -rejectReservedKeys(data, ctx)   <<REUSE — now also rejects is_stub -> 400>>
}

' ===========================================================================
' META LAYER  (src/meta/) — the stub marker round-trip (mirrors depends_on)
' ===========================================================================
package "meta (src/meta)" {

  class "ddl.js" as Ddl {
    +PG_TYPE_MAP : Record   <<REUSE>>
    +createTableSql(def) : string   <<REUSE — framework cols suffice for a stub>>
    +alterColumnsSql(def, existingCols) : string   <<REUSE — upgrade with existingCols=[] (IF NOT EXISTS)>>
  }

  class "installer.js" as Inst {
    +emitMigration(def) : string   <<REUSE>>
    +syncDoctype(def, store)   <<EDIT: write is_stub on the DocType row>>
    +migrate(def, store, opts)   <<EDIT: 4-branch upgrade/fresh/downgrade-noop/reinstall>>
    +bumpMetaVersion(store)   <<REUSE>>
  }

  class "boot-meta.js" as Boot {
    +META_DOCTYPES   <<EDIT: add {fieldname:'is_stub', fieldtype:'Check'} to DocType>>
    +registerBootMeta()   <<REUSE>>
  }

  class "loader.js" as Loader {
    +ensure(doctype, store)   <<REUSE>>
    +load(doctype, store) : Meta   <<EDIT: read row.is_stub -> Meta>>
    -_primeDoctype(...)   <<REUSE — splits Table/Link, loader.js:203-211>>
    -_primeLinkTarget(...)   <<REUSE — a stub primes like any other>>
  }

  class "registry.js" as Reg {
    +getMeta / hasMeta / setMeta   <<REUSE>>
    +FieldDef / DocMeta typedefs   <<EDIT: add isStub? to DocMeta>>
  }

  class "Meta (meta.js)" as Meta {
    +doctype / table / fields / issingle ...   <<REUSE>>
    +isStub : boolean   <<NEW: this._isStub + get isStub()>>
  }
}

' ===========================================================================
' RUNTIME LAYER  (src/runtime/) — THE CRUX: soft-link validation into a stub
' ===========================================================================
package "runtime (src/runtime)" {

  class "links.js" as Links {
    +resolveFetchFrom(meta, doc, store)   <<REUSE — empty stub table -> silent no-op>>
    +validateLinks(meta, doc, store)   <<EDIT: SOFT-LINK skip when target Meta.isStub>>
    -tryMeta(doctype) : Meta|null   <<REUSE>>
  }

  class "document.js" as Doc {
    +save() / insert()   <<REUSE — calls validateLinks unchanged>>
    -#saveChildren()   <<REUSE — writes child rows; WHY Table targets must be FULL>>
  }
}

' ===========================================================================
' RELATIONSHIPS
' ===========================================================================
CLI ..> Sel        : planInstall(seeds, root)
CLI ..> E2D        : erpnextJsonToDef (full) / makeStubDef (link stubs)
CLI ..> Inst       : emitMigration | migrate (per def)
Sel  --> Plan      : returns
E2D  ..> FTM       : mapFieldtype (full defs only)

Inst ..> Ddl       : createTableSql / alterColumnsSql(existingCols=[])
Inst ..> Boot      : registerBootMeta
Inst ..> Doc       : syncDoctype via newDoc('DocType').save()
Boot --> Reg       : primeFrom (pins DocType incl. is_stub col)

Loader ..> Reg     : setMeta(isStub)
Loader --> Meta    : new Meta({ ..., isStub })
Doc  ..> Links     : validateLinks(meta, doc, store)
Links ..> Reg      : tryMeta(target) -> reads target.isStub
ReqS ..> Doc       : envelope gate BEFORE updateDoc (handler.js)

note bottom of Links
  THE CORRECTNESS DECISION (ADR E2):
  validateLinks skips the row-existence check iff target.isStub === true
  (SOFT link — trust the value). A Link into a FULL (non-stub) target keeps
  the HARD check. Gated on the TARGET, so a stub can NEVER soften a Link into
  a fully-generated doctype. Recovers automatically when the stub upgrades.
end note

note bottom of ReqS
  E2-TRUST CONDITION (privilege hole): is_stub softens link integrity.
  Add it to RESERVED_KEYS so a client POST {is_stub:true} -> 400.
  Only the installer (syncDoctype, bypasses the envelope) writes it.
end note

note bottom of Inst
  STUB -> FULL UPGRADE (ADR E5), read is_stub from tabDocType (no DDL introspection):
    1 UPGRADE (exists && wasStub): alterColumnsSql(def,[]) -> syncDoctype is_stub=false -> bump
    2 FRESH   (!exists):           createTableSql -> sync -> bump
    3 DOWNGRADE NO-OP (full && def.isStub): return skipped — NEVER DDL, NEVER re-flip is_stub  [cond a]
    4 RE-INSTALL FULL: createTableSql (IF NOT EXISTS no-op) -> sync
  PgAdmin stays WRITE-ONLY — existingCols=[] is safe (ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS)  [cond b]
end note

note bottom of Plan
  E3 EDGE-KIND SPLIT (critique blocker fix):
  Table/Table-MultiSelect children carry the seed's DATA -> FULL + transitive.
  Only LINK targets -> stub. Quotation: ~9 full (parent + 8 children) +
  Link targets stubbed (tens, not 298). Frappe-core 20 are all Links -> safe.
end note

@enduml
